ownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528107\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528107\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gzq1665702785696.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gzq1665702785696.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gzq1665702785696.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gzq1665702785696\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Start the Uniface IDE</h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can start the Uniface IDE from the default shortcut, or you can define your own\n      shortcut with different command line parameters.</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"gzq1665702785696__context_w1531ab1b5b1_w1532ab1b5_w1533ab1\">By default, the Uniface\n         IDE is automatically installed and configured to use SQLite as the Repository. If you\n         configure Uniface to use another database, the database must be running before starting the\n         IDE.</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gzq1665702785696__li_d1274e1_d1275e1_d1276e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"gzq1665702785696__p_d3566e1_d3567e1_d3568e1\">Start the Uniface IDE from the default shortcut\n               created during installation.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\"> By default, the command line dialog is displayed, so that you can instruct the\n                  IDE to perform a specific action or use a different configuration. Uniface\n                  remembers previously used command line parameters, so you can also choose a\n                  command line from the drop-drown list.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"gzq1665702785696__fig_d3569e1_d3570e1_d3571e1\">\n<img alt=\"Command Line dialog\" class=\"image\" id=\"gzq1665702785696__image_vlj_gvx_3zb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/commandlinedialog.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"gzq1665702785696__note_w1542ab1b5b3b1b3b3_w1543ab1b5b3b1b3_w1544ab1b5b3b1_w1545ab1b5b3_w1546ab1b5_w1547ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> This dialog is displayed because the shortcut for the Uniface IDE\n                  specifies a question mark parameter (<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"esg1665702785765.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/esg1665702785765.html\" title=\"Causes the command line dialog to be displayed.\">?</a>) in its\n                  command line. You can edit this shortcut or create your own with different command\n                  line switches.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gzq1665702785696__li_d1277e1_d1278e1_d1279e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"gzq1665702785696__p_d3572e1_d3573e1_d3574e1\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> to continue.\n At startup, Uniface checks whether the default templates are available in the Repository. If they are not found, you are prompted to load them. The defaults mustbe loaded in your Repository.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gzq1665702785696__p_d3575e1_d3576e1_d3577e1\">If you want to import an alternative set of\n                  templates, click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Browse</span> button to find and import\n                  them.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hxc1665702744973.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Command Line Interface</a><p>Uniface provides a command line interface that enables you to access many functions without actually opening the user interface. By running a Uniface executable (such as ide.exe or uniface) with command line switches you can compile objects, debug applications, import and export, specify assignment files, and more.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nry1665702619485.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Default Templates</a><p>Uniface provides a default set of templates and snippets that enable you to create new development objects and components that can work immediately. In fact, it is not possible to create a new object without a template.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528107\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528107\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Start the Uniface IDE Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Start the Uniface IDE You can start the Uniface IDE from the default shortcut, or you can define your own shortcut with different command line parameters. By default, the Uniface IDE is automatically installed and configured to use SQLite as the Repository. If you configure Uniface to use another database, the database must be running before starting the IDE. Start the Uniface IDE from the default shortcut created during installation. By default, the command line dialog is displayed, so that you can instruct the IDE to perform a specific action or use a different configuration. Uniface remembers previously used command line parameters, so you can also choose a command line from the drop-drown list. Note: This dialog is displayed because the shortcut for the Uniface IDE specifies a question mark parameter ( ? ) in its command line. You can edit this shortcut or create your own with different command line switches. Click OK to continue. At startup, Uniface checks whether the default templates are available in the Repository. If they are not found, you are prompted to load them. The defaults mustbe loaded in your Repository. If you want to import an alternative set of templates, click the Browse button to find and import them. Related Links Uniface Command Line Interface Uniface provides a command line interface that enables you to access many functions without actually opening the user interface. By running a Uniface executable (such as ide.exe or uniface) with command line switches you can compile objects, debug applications, import and export, specify assignment files, and more. Uniface Default Templates Uniface provides a default set of templates and snippets that enable you to create new development objects and components that can work immediately. In fact, it is not possible to create a new object without a template. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}